\begin_layout Subsection
Up and Running
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All you need to run Prudence is a JVM: version 7 or above is recommended,
 though 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "version 6"
target "http://threecrickets.com/prudence/download/#jvm6"

\end_inset

 can also be supported.
 You do not need then 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Enterprise Edition
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 nor even a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

JDK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

: Prudence needs only the basic JVM runtime.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are two ways to get Prudence: the easiest way is to download the distribut
ion, which includes most everything and is ready to rumble.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Let's do that now"
target "http://threecrickets.com/prudence/download/#distribution"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But Prudence is modular: later on, you may prefer to assemble your own distribut
ion using the 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Sincerity packaging and bootstrapping tool"
target "http://threecrickets.com/sincerity/"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

