First Steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You've played with the example applications, and now it's time to create
 your own.
 Let's make a wiki!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

prudence create
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Create a new application using the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

prudence
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 Sincerity command:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

sincerity prudence create wiki
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Restart Prudence, and you should be able to see your new application at
 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "http://localhost:8080/wiki/"
target "http://localhost:8080/wiki/"

\end_inset

.
 There's not much to see at this point.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Our Application's Subdirectory
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let's take a look at our application.
 Its files are all under 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/component/applications/wiki/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At the root are three JavaScript files used to configure the application.
 Take a look at 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

routing.js
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

setting.js
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 The former defines your application's URI-space, while the latter controls
 its general behavior.
 Note that Prudence's (and Sincerity's) configuration philosophy is to use
 JavaScript wherever possible, which allows for dynamic, flexible configurations
 that adapt to the environment in which they are run.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Resources
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/resources/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 subdirectory is mapped directly to your URI-space, just like most standard
 web servers.
 For example, a file named 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/mydir/myfile.html
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 will be mapped to 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "http://localhost:8080/wiki/mydir/myfile.html"
target "http://localhost:8080/wiki/mydir/myfile.html"

\end_inset

.
 Also like standard web servers, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

index.html
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 will be mapped to the directory itself.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Actually, you'll notice that our root index is named 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

index.s.html
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 We call that 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

s
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 a pre-extension: here, it stands for 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

scriptlet,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and tells Prudence that this is a text file that may include one or more
 sections of code called 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

scriptlets,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 which are delimited by 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

<%
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

%>
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 This, again, may be familiar to you: it's similar to how PHP, JSP and ASP
 work.
 (We'll just quickly let you know that Prudence can automatically cache
 these scriptlet pages, with powerful, fine-grained control over fragmentation
 and cache keys, and configurable cache backends.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Under 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/resources/style/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 you'll see 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

site.zuss
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "ZUSS"
target "https://github.com/tomyeh/ZUSS"

\end_inset

 is an extended CSS language, inspired by 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "LESS"
target "http://lesscss.org/"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "SASS"
target "http://sass-lang.com/"

\end_inset

.
 Prudence will automatically recognize the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

.zuss
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 extension and create the CSS for us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Libraries
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our reusable code is all under the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/libraries/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 subdirectory.
 Specifically, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/libraries/includes/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 contains fragments that can be included into our scriptlet pages.
 You'll see that our 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

index.s.html
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 uses them.
 For example:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<%& '/header/' %>
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\SpecialChar \ldots{}
includes the file 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/libraries/includes/header.html
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Note that included files may have scriptlets in them (and can be cached
 independently).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All the above might seem quite familiar to you, and this is by intention.
 But the files under 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/libraries/dispatched/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 may seem strange: they are 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

low-level
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 direct implementations of encapsulated RESTful resources.
 Take a look at 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

example.js
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moreover, these kinds of RESTful resources are not directly mapped to URIs
 like those in the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/resources/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 subdirectory.
 Instead, they are 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

dispatched
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 using unique IDs.
 In Prudence, this paradigm is called 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

URI/resource separation,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and it allows you full flexibility in structuring your code vs.
 structuring your URI-space.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We'll get into all that as we go along this tutorial.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Scriptlets
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let's look more closely at our 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

index.s.html
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 page.
 The scriptlets are executed, while what's outside the scriptlets is simply
 output to the HTTP response.
 You can freely mix regular output and scriptlets:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<% for (var x = 0; x < 10; x++ ) { %>
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<p>These are 10 paragraphs.</p>
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<% } %>
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are also a few shortcut scriptlets.
 For example, to output an expression:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<%= x*2 %>
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The above is equivalent to:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<% print(x*2) %>
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Also useful is the inclusion scriptlet, which we've already discussed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<%& '/header/' %>
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The above is equivalent to:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

<% document.include('/header/') %>
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behind the scenes, Prudence parses 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

index.s.html
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and turns it into JavaScript source code.
 If you'd like to see the generated code, look at the Scripturian cache,
 specifically under the container's 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/cache/scripturian/container/component/applications/wiki/resources/
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 directory.
 These generated files are not actually used by Prudence, and only available
