 old.
 The first hit would thus need to generate and cache the page, which is
 much slower than using the cached version.
 For very large applications optimized for caching, a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

cold
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 cache can cause serious problems: see the discussion in 
\bar under
Scaling Tips (page 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand pageref
reference "scaling-tips-cache-warming"

\end_inset

)
\bar default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To avoid the delay, it's recommended that you ready your resources by hitting
 them as soon as Prudence starts up.
 This happens in two phases:
\end_layout

