\begin_layout Subsection
Cookies
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "cookies"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Cookies represent a small client-side database, which the server can use
 to retrieve or store per-client data.
 Not all clients support cookies, and even those that do (most web browsers)
 might have the feature disabled, so it's not always good idea to rely on
 cookies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
From the Client
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Retrieve a specific cookie from those the client send you according to its
 name using 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "conversation.getCookie"
target "http://threecrickets.com/api/javascript/?namespace=conversation&item=conversation.getCookie"

\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

var session = conversation.getCookie('session')
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

if (null !== session) {
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

	print(session.value)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or use 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "conversation.cookies"
target "http://threecrickets.com/api/javascript/?namespace=conversation&item=conversation.cookies"

\end_inset

 to iterate through all available cookies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following attributes are available:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
name: (read only)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
version: (integer) per a specific cookie
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
value: textual, or text-encoded binary data (note that most clients have
 strict limits on how much total data is allowed to be stored in all cookies
 per domain)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
domain: the client should only use the cookie with this domain and its subdomain
s (web browsers will not let you set a cookie for a domain which is not
 the domain of the request or a subdomain of it)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
path: the client should only use the cookie with URIs that begin with this
 path (“/”, the default, would mean to use it with all URIs)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
To the Client
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can ask that a client modify any of the cookies you've retrieved 
\emph on
from
\emph default
 it, upon a successful response, by calling the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

save
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

