\begin_layout Subsubsection
Changing the Request
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It may be useful to change user requests for testing purposes.
 Specifically, we can affect content negotiation by changing the accepted
 formats declared by the user.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example, let's say we want to disable compression for all resources,
 even if clients declare that they are capable of handling it:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

function handleBefore(conversation) {
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

	conversation.client.acceptedEncodings.clear()
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

	return 'continue'
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Easy! Note that this would be 
\emph on
much
\emph default
 harder to achieve retroactively, by changing the response: we would have
 to decompress all compressed responses.
 Some effects are much better implemented in handleBefore.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Overriding the Response
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Filters can be useful for overriding the response under certain conditions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following example always sets the response to a web page displaying
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

blocked!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, unless a special 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

admin
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\bar under
