 You would then need to decode, disassemble, make your changes, and then
 reassemble such responses, which is neither trivial nor efficient.
 
\emph on
Content
\emph default
 filtering should best be handled at the level of the resource code itself,
 
\emph on
before 
\emph default
the response payload is created.
\end_layout

